## Apple Pay and Google Pay Integration

Apple Pay and Google Pay buttons provide a seamless and secure way for your customers to complete transactions. Depending on your implementation method, follow the appropriate steps for either **Redirect** or **IFRAME**.  
**Note:** Additional domain verification and script requirements apply only to **Apple Pay** in an **IFRAME** implementation. **Google Pay** does not require these steps.

---

### Redirect Implementation

If your [**payment page**🛈](#introduction/pay-protocol "Learn how to create a payment page") uses a **Redirect**, integrating Apple Pay and Google Pay is simple:

1. **Enable in the Merchant Console:**
   - Navigate to the [**Merchant Console**](https://pay.hyp.co.il/p/?action=login "Hypay").
   - Go to the "Settings" menu.
   - Enable Apple Pay and Google Pay options.
   - Alternatively, contact your sales representative for assistance.

2. **Automatic Button Display:**
   - Once enabled, the Apple Pay and Google Pay buttons will appear automatically on your payment page.
   - **Note:** Neither Apple Pay nor Google Pay require additional setup when using the **Redirect** method.
   
#### Hiding Payment Buttons

If you need to prevent the Apple Pay, Google Pay, Bit or any other active payment buttons from appearing on the payment page, you can control this behaviour via the Pay Protocol. Add the parameter **hideBtns** to your API call. When `hideBtns=True`, all of the payment buttons that are currently enabled for the terminal will be hidden on the payment page. If you omit the parameter or pass any value other than `True`, the buttons will be displayed as usual.

This setting does not affect the backend payment processing – it only hides the buttons in the user interface.


---

### IFRAME Implementation

If your payment page is displayed within an **IFRAME**, additional steps are required specifically for **Apple Pay**:

1. **Enable in the Merchant Console:**
   - Navigate to the [**Merchant Console**](https://pay.hyp.co.il/p/?action=login "Hypay").
   - Go to the "Settings" menu.
   - Enable Apple Pay and Google Pay options.
   - Alternatively, contact your sales representative for assistance.

2. **Domain Verification (Apple Pay Only):**
   - Download the Apple Pay verification file from the following URL: [Download Verification File](https://icom.yaad.net/cgi-bin/yaadpay/applepay_main.pl?action=DownloadVerFile)
   - Upload this file to the following directory on your website:
     ```
     https://yourdomain.com/.well-known/apple-developer-merchantid-domain-association
     ```

3. **Include the Required Script (Apple Pay Only):**
   - Add the following script to the `<head>` section of your website:
     ```html
     <script src="https://pps.creditguard.co.il/plugins/applePayOnIframe.js"></script>
     ```

4. **HTTPS Requirement (Apple Pay Only):**
   - Ensure your domain is HTTPS-enabled before proceeding with the domain verification process.

5. **Adding the Domain in the Interface (Apple Pay Only):**
   - After the domain is verified, go to the "Apple Pay" section in the "Settings" menu of the [**Merchant Console**](https://pay.hyp.co.il/p/?action=login "Hypay").
   - Add the domain under the "Apple Pay" section to complete the configuration.

6. **Confirming Button Appearance:**
   - After adding the domain, check your payment page within the IFRAME to confirm that the **Apple Pay** button appears and functions correctly.
   - **Note:** This step is not required for Google Pay, as it does not rely on domain verification or script inclusion.

---

#### Notes
- For **Apple Pay** in an **IFRAME**, the button will not function properly until all steps, including script addition and domain verification, are completed.
- **Google Pay** does not require domain verification or script inclusion, regardless of the implementation method.
- The domain verification process for Apple Pay is a one-time setup. However, changes to your domain or hosting may require re-verification.
- Ensure that all configuration steps are completed before attempting a live transaction with Apple Pay.
- For **Google Pay** inside an IFRAME, ensure the embedding `<iframe>` includes `allow="payment"` and the boolean `allowpaymentrequest` attribute. Without these, the Google Pay button may not appear or will fail to open the payment sheet.

## Transaction J5

If a [pay request](https://Hypay.docs.apiary.io/#introduction/pay-protocol)/[soft request](https://Hypay.docs.apiary.io/#introduction/soft-protocol-transaction-in-web-server) was made with parameter J5=True and parameter MoreData=True.
There are two methods to implement a charge of the J5 transaction.

---

### If Amount of charge equal or less from Amount J5 Transaction
If you want to charge a same transaction with same amount or amount less from amount J5 transaction - you can do it with soft request with additional parameters.

---
### Reference url is:
https://pay.hyp.co.il/p?
<br>+<br>
[Token flow subject](https://Hypay.docs.apiary.io/#introduction/tokens) parameters
<br>+<br>
Additional parameters

---


###Additional parameters:
|Parameter name | Description | Value format | Required | General |
|---------------|-------------|--------------|----------|---------|
| inputObj.originalUid | UID unique value recieve from response after successful transaction from request with action pay/soft | Numeric | Required | |
| inputObj.originalAmount | Amount should be equal or less from amount J5 transaction | Numeric<br><b>500</b> - Equals to 5 Shekels | Required | |
| AuthNum | Approval from credit card company <br> value equal to parameter ACode from response <br> after successful pay | Numeric | Required | |
| inputObj.authorizationCodeManpik | defualt Static SHVA parameter | 7 | Required | |

### If Amount of charge is bigger from Amount J5 Transaction
If you want to charge a same transaction with amount bigger from amount J5 transaction - you need follow [Token flow subject](https://Hypay.docs.apiary.io/#introduction/tokens) without additional parameters.

<br><br><br><br>

